2 Using theCrag - 5 Searching

<p>On any page in the top right corner you'll find the ubiquitious search box.
Using the adjacent drop-down menu you can choose to search for:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Routes and areas all over the world</li>
	<li>Routes and areas in the area you're currently visiting</li>
	<li>Climbers</li>
</ul>


<h2>Advanced search</h2>

<p>Coming soon: Advanced search filters, eg search for routes within a range of grades, stars, style, height etc</p>


<h2>Search directly in your browser from anywhere on the internet</h2>

<p>For the hardcore search fanatics you can setup theCrag as a custom search directly in your browser. Now finding a route will never be more than one click away!</p>


<h4>IE7+</h4>
<p>Simply click the menu option next to the search icon and select 'Search theCrag'</p>
<p><img width="458" height="380" src="/static/cids/images/opensearch-ie-1.1.0.jpg"></p>


<h4>FireFox</h4>
<p>Simple click the menu drop down next to the search bar and select 'Search theCrag'</p>
<p><img width="458" height="380" src="/static/cids/images/opensearch-ff-1.1.0.jpg"></p>


<h4>Chrome</h4>
<p>Click the Spanner > Options, under Manage Search Engines find theCrag.com and click 'Make default'</p>


